# Vision Affichage v2 — environment variables
#
# Copy to `.env.local` and fill in. `.env.local` is gitignored.

# ─── Plausible analytics (Loi 25 compliant — gated on user consent) ──────────
# Operator sets these to enable analytics; until set, no script loads and no
# network request is made. The Plausible script is also gated client-side on
# `hasConsent('analytics')` (see components/Analytics.tsx) — declining or
# leaving the consent banner unanswered means no script tag is rendered.
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_PLAUSIBLE_DOMAIN: the domain registered in your Plausible
#   dashboard (e.g. `visionaffichage.com`). Leave blank to disable analytics.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_PLAUSIBLE_SCRIPT_URL: defaults to https://plausible.io/js/script.js
#   Override only if self-hosting Plausible or using a custom proxy.
NEXT_PUBLIC_PLAUSIBLE_DOMAIN=
NEXT_PUBLIC_PLAUSIBLE_SCRIPT_URL=https://plausible.io/js/script.js
